PHASE 1: PROBLEM VERIFICATION
==============================
Source: Research doc + cross-verification against our codebase

PROBLEM 1: "Microsecond latency" — VERIFIED
  - AI workloads create facility-scale power spikes (citation verified)
  - 100,000+ H100 GPUs × 700W TDP = synchronized demand swings of 100+ MW
  - Tesla Autobidder designed for MINUTE-level energy trading, NOT microsecond response
  - Gas turbines suffer voltage flicker → fries $30K H100 chips
  - Our code addresses this via PREDICTIVE approach (not reactive) — predict 10 min ahead

PROBLEM 2: Grid-Supercomputer co-optimization — VERIFIED
  - xAI & Tesla Energy are separate companies with separate software stacks
  - $430M Megapack sales to xAI in 2025 — but integration is REACTIVE, not predictive
  - $2B investment for "potential AI collaborations" — integration NOT complete
  - MIT TopoOpt confirms compute+energy co-optimization is open research area
  - Our code addresses this via CoOptimizer + SignalEngine + Trainer pipeline

PROBLEM 3: Weather nowcasting — PARTIALLY VERIFIED
  - Google GraphCast/GenCast excellent at DAYS-level, weak at 60-second nowcasting
  - Immediate relevance is LOW for xAI (Memphis site runs on gas turbines, not solar)
  - Will become CRITICAL when xAI shifts to renewable-heavy grid mix
  - Our code has solar/wind/cloud features but no real-time weather API integration

CONFIDENCE SCORES (1-10):
  Problem 1: 10/10 — Direct xAI threat, well-documented
  Problem 2: 8/10 — Real but co-optimization scope is debatable
  Problem 3: 6/10 — Real but not urgent for current xAI deployment
